                <h1>Chiropractic: A Brief History and Evolution</h1>
                <p>The history of chiropractic dates back to the late 19th century when Daniel David Palmer performed the first spinal adjustment in 1895. He founded the Palmer School of Chiropractic, emphasizing the connection between the spine and overall health. Over the years, chiropractic evolved into a recognized healthcare profession, focusing on spinal manipulation and holistic approaches.</p>
